The paper deals with the problem of recognizing regular languages in a streaming model of computation, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also introduces a new variant of the streaming model, called the sliding window model, and combines it with the property testing setting. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IT (Information Theory), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topics covered in the paper.
